Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then halve lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Cut the @halloumi{250%g} block widthways into slices 1cm thick.

Pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml} into a #bowl{}, season with @salt and @pepper and add the @olive oil{2%tsp}. Mix well, then add the tomatoes to the bowl and mix again. Set aside, we will add the lettuce to this bowl later.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil in #large frying pan{} over medium high heat. When hot, add the halloumi slices. Cook until browned, about ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn carefully and repeat on the other side, another ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, mix the @harissa paste{50%g} and @honey{15%ml} together in a #small bowl{}. Once the halloumi is browned, remove the pan from the heat and add the harissa and honey. Turn the halloumi to coat in the mixture.

Meanwhile, warm the @plain naans{2} in the oven for ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the baby gem to the bowl with the dressing and tomatoes. Toss to coat and get ready to serve.

Place a naan on each #plate{} and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Top with the salad and then the halloumi slices. Drizzle on any leftover dressing and any honey harissa that is left behind in the pan. Enjoy!